messages.message: Hey, i’ve seen the postman collection has been updated to add the Batch APIs, can we make these the default options and move the old filesystems ones into a folder and make it clear they aren’t the recommended approach anymore? At the moment it looks like the batch ones are the secondary option.

Also the postman doesn’t set the ib-context header. So people are defaulting to the requests going to their community plan.

Can we make a different folder to break out the two different contexts?
